   KINGSTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Twenty five countries in the Caribbean Basin have signed an agreement to
create the Association of Caribbean States (ACS) trade grouping, writes
Canute James in Kingston. The ACS has a market of 200m people and includes
Colombia, Mexico and Venezuela, the countries of Central America, Cuba, the
Dominican Republic, Haiti and Suriname and the 13 members of the Caribbean
Community.
