<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JUL 94 / Indian arms talks in Moscow
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A senior military delegation from India arrived in Moscow yesterday for
talks on co-operation with Russia and possible aircraft purchases, Itar-Tass
news agency reported. The delegation, led by air force Commander-in-Chief S
K Kaul, would meet senior defence ministry and arms industry officials
during the one-week visit and examine the latest models of Russian combat
aircraft. 'He (Kaul) is also likely to negotiate purchases of MiG-29
fighter-bombers and SU-30 multi-purpose fighters,' the agency said, adding
that India might consider buying a licence to make SU-30s. The two sides
will also discuss modernisation of MiG-21 fighters in service with the
Indian air force and creation of a joint Russian-Indian aircraft venture,
Tass said, quoting an Indian embassy official. Russia and India agreed to
step up military co-operation in a joint declaration signed by President
Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister P V Narasimha Rao during a visit by the
latter to Moscow last month. Russia was India's biggest arms supplier in the
Soviet era, but sales have slumped since then.
</TEXT>
