FT  25 JUL 94 / World News in Brief: Atherton fined by England selectors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
England cricket captain Mike Atherton denied having tampered with the ball
during the Test match against South Africa, but admitted not giving a full
explanation of his actions to the match referee. Ray Illingworth, England
chairman of selectors, fined him Pounds 1,000 for using dirt to dry his
fingers and a further Pounds 1,000 for not explaining his actions fully. The
fines followed South Africa's triumphant return to Lord's, where they beat
England by 356 runs with a day to spare.
